    {
      "id": "ddc12137-b1d2-4aa5-abdb-9085a38f65b9",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $(u_n)$ une série convergente à termes positifs décroissants.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\((u_n)\\)</span> une série convergente à termes positifs décroissants.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "9c480f47-cd4a-4ff5-a237-99f6d9339beb",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $nu_n\\to 0$ lorsque $n\\to\\infty$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(nu_n\\to 0\\)</span> lorsque <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\to\\infty\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "bc189ff5-758a-4f08-a429-931c4eebbb41",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$nu_{2n} \\le \\sum_{k=n+1}^{2n} u_k$,\n             $nu_{2n+1} \\le \\sum_{k=n+2}^{2n+1} u_k$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(nu_{2n} \\le \\sum_{k=n+1}^{2n} u_k\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(nu_{2n+1} \\le \\sum_{k=n+2}^{2n+1} u_k\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2776da51-6994-439c-9155-94781b775ead",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $\\sum_{u_k \\ge 1/n} \\frac 1{u_k} = \\text{o}(n^2)$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\sum_{u_k \\ge 1/n} \\frac 1{u_k} = \\text{o}(n^2)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "88b04c64-3b82-4325-a48e-29d8bcaebe19",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\varepsilon > 0$ : Pour $k$ suffisament grand,\n             $u_k \\le \\frac \\varepsilon k$,\n             donc $u_k \\ge \\frac 1n  \\Rightarrow  k\\le n\\varepsilon$.\n             Alors $\\sum_{u_k \\ge 1/n} \\frac 1{u_k} \\le n^2\\varepsilon + Kn$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\varepsilon &gt; 0\\)</span> : Pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(k\\)</span> suffisament grand, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(u_k \\le \\frac \\varepsilon k\\)</span>, donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(u_k \\ge \\frac 1n  \\Rightarrow  k\\le n\\varepsilon\\)</span>. Alors <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\sum_{u_k \\ge 1/n} \\frac 1{u_k} \\le n^2\\varepsilon + Kn\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
}